In tcsh I use

set time='3 Time: %Uuser %Ssystem %Esec (=%P%%),  %X+%DkB  %I+%Oio %Fpf+%Ww'

which gives me information on all jobs which last longer than 3 seconds.
How can I achieve this in zsh? (Did not find something in the man-pages). 

